Class BinarySearchTree<T extends algorithms.heapsAndPQs.HeapNode>

  • java.lang.Object
    • algorithms.BinarySearchTree<T>

  • public class BinarySearchTree<T extends algorithms.heapsAndPQs.HeapNode>
extends java.lang.Object
    Binary Search Tree â€“ has the property that for every node: The left subtree contains only nodes that have a key less than or equal to the node The right subtree contains only nodes that have a key greater than the node The left and right subtrees are also binary search trees use a Node with left, right and parent. use a binary search method impl as: while loop rot != null: if (root.value .lt. value) root=root.getRight()... adapted upon pseudocode from Cormen et al. Introduction to Algorithms. added in-order, pre-order and post-order traversal methods. the delete method has been changed from the book. Also note that the class can currently only hold unique keys.

    nichole

        protected T[] getInOrderTraversalIterative(T node)
